comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-18T21:58:24.218Z",claude-code-agent,"Triage (during pm-ldr1/GH-157 work): GH-244 is CLOSED on GitHub — resolved in #254 (commit 0447c6e4) by surfacing provider_source/vector_store_source + persisted *_configured values in pm health, so auto-detected providers are no longer misreported as 'not configured'. The narrower 'persist the resolved provider/adapter strings back into settings.json' idea is DECLINED: writing settings.json on every read risks the governance persist-trap (cf pm-haak file-backed-schema leak) and churns the file under VCS. Recommend closing as resolved-by-#254 in a NON-release-bearing touch (closing here would mis-bucket the changelog since the fix already shipped). Related: [[pm-ldr1]] search ergonomics."
notes[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-19T20:57:11.856Z",claude-code-agent,"Verified GH-244 is already fully implemented and the GitHub issue is CLOSED. resolveProviderConfigSource() (src/core/search/providers.ts:61) classifies configured|auto-detected|unconfigured, and pm health surfaces provider_configured/provider_source + vector_store_configured/vector_store_source in the vectorization check (src/cli/commands/health.ts:1518-1533), so a config audit can tell an auto-detected empty provider/adapter apart from a genuine misconfiguration. No code change required."
  "2026-06-19T21:20:03.881Z",claude-code-agent,"Reopened in PR #306: GH-244 is verified already-shipped (#254, commit 0447c6e4). Closing this item in a release-bearing PR mis-buckets the CHANGELOG (CodeRabbit + prior triage both flagged it would list GH-244 under the next release's Fixed though the fix already shipped). Close only in a NON-release-bearing touch. The verification of the implementation stands."
  "2026-06-23T12:51:17.536Z",claude-code-agent,"Re-opened: CodeRabbit (PR #349) correctly flagged that closing this verified-already-shipped tracker inside a release-bearing PR mis-buckets pm-changelog (the GH-244 fix shipped in v2026.6.19 / #254, so listing it under a later release is misleading). Keep OPEN; close in a dedicated NON-release-bearing touch, per the existing triage note and prior practice (cf pm-sdbo/pm-28cf history)."
body: "## Context\nTracks GitHub issue #244 follow-up. After runtime auto-detection, empty-string search.provider / vector_store.adapter values persist in settings and read as misleading \"configured but blank\" state instead of not-configured.\n\n## Approach\nNormalize on read AND write: treat \"\"/whitespace as absent in the settings loader (settings validator STRIPS unknown keys already — extend to normalize empties), and stop persisting empty strings from the auto-detect path. Surface the normalized value in pm config get and doctor so agents see 'auto' / unset, not \"\".\n\n## Definition of done\nSetting provider/adapter to \"\" then reading returns not-configured; auto-detect no longer writes empty strings; GH-244 closed with a comment linking the shipped release; spec covers load-normalize and write paths."
